cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with optimization and projection algorithms, which are commonly studied in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of upper bounds and criteria for ordering constraints suggests information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the application of the projection methods to make predictions implies a connection to statistics (cs.SI).
